5:
Why not? At least let me pay for the
tea.
13:
Hey, Libram. You can pay for ME
whenever you want.
16:
THIS is why, Libram. You will be
admired not for your character, but
for your purse.
17:
Bridges built on a foundation of
money are soon to fall.
19:
There you go with the preaching
again. Not everything needs to have
a moral, you know.
23:
Is this why you turned down my offer
of financial aid?
25:
However... As a champion, you must
believe it is the duty of the strong to
aid the weak.
27:
Well, I too have strength—not in
warfare, but in commerce. In
rejecting the sole source of my
power, are you not rejecting me as
well?
39:
Then it's settled! Tomorrow, I shall fill
your coffers with gold!
45: Stella, what say you as Keeper of—
54:
N-no. I only... I only forgot the time.
There is an appointment I must
keep!
62:
Azrail... Brother... No. Your lordship. It
has been many moons since our
last meeting.
65:
I must have surprised you at the
tavern. I apologize. But it was
imperative that this meeting remain
secret...
66:
Today, we decide the future of our
house.
68:
There is much to be discussed. The
Guild has prepared a manor for us. I
shall be waiting for you there.
72: The storm has finally found me...
81:
I am the third son of the House of
Swes. I have always been
considered the child of the
family—someone to be indulged,
but ultimately, discounted.
82:
And yet, the eldest son, Azrail—who
will one day be head of our
house—has traveled many leagues
to find me... Why?
84:
Because the House of Swes desires
information on you.
87:
I refused them once and paid the
price in blood.
94:
At the moment, I still did not know
my own heart.
97: But now I do. You... are my friends.
99:
I will not sell out my friends... nor
Palpebra.
101:
I do not wish to pave the path to a
war between this city and my
homeland.
106: Is there anything WE can do?
109:
Yes. I will meet my brother tonight.
Come with me.
111:
I... am frightened. Not of my brother,
but of myself. I have long desired his
favor, and I do not know what price I
will pay to gain it.
112:
Azrail will not be told who you are, of
course. You will be disguised as
hired guards. I only ask—
117: We will be there for you.
122:
Yeah! And if it comes to a fight... We
have your back.
130:
You believed I desired information
from you? And that I would take it...
by force?
136:
If I truly wished to conquer Palpebra,
do you think I would travel all the
way here—with no guards—to talk?
137:
In any case, you have refused me
for all the right reasons. I see now
that you possess the golden heart of
the Swes.
142:
Did you not send the Kwetur's hired
blades after me?
145:
No. Rather, I received reports that
you were after MY life. I never trusted
them but...
147:
I see now that, among us brothers,
there must be a traitor. No other
could compel my retainers to lie to
me.
150:
Do you mean to say that Ziggurat
would...
152:
Libram, you must cut off all contact
with the Swes. Go into hiding.
153:
A crack has formed in our house. If it
falls, I do not wish you buried
beneath the rubble.
159:
You have made a life for yourself
here. Live it.
160:
Despite the many leagues between
you and our homeland, you have
remained a true Swes... I am proud
of you, Libram.
171:
The same as it's always been.
Establish a trade route between my
country and Palpebra.
172:
Perhaps it will be the key to peace
between my brothers.
175:
You aren't alone, Libram. I'm sure
there's tons of people here who'll be
happy to help.
178:
Of course. I always pay the worthy a
handsome reward for their service.
183:
With what money, though? Didn't
you cut off all contact with your
family?
184:
I'm assumin' that's where the dough
came from.
189:
There... There is no cause for
concern!
192:
I have some coin on me. And what's
more, I have a golden heart! THAT is
all you need to be rich in, friends!
194:
Hah. Just you wait. Soon, the name
of Libram will be ringing in every
corner of Palpebra!
